transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, I am a recipient of Scorablue. I need to cancel my subscription as I'm having some—

Speaker 2: Uncomfortable and adverse side effects. Give me your zip code.

Speaker 1: 32086. What's your first and last name?

Speaker 2: Michael. Last name is Gauf. G-A-U-F.

Speaker 1: Alrighty, I do got you pulled up here, sir. I do understand you said you had some side—

Speaker 2: Effects here. Obviously, we can't cancel this for you, but we do have another viagra that—

Speaker 1: Has been made over the last 10 years here to get rid of most of those adverse side effects—

Speaker 2: Like headaches, runny nose, flustered feeling. Yeah, what I'm having is, I'm having feelings—

Speaker 1: Of sort of like increased anxiety and almost like I've been drinking coffee all day. And—

Speaker 2: I have high blood pressure, so I'm going to back out of everything for right now.

Speaker 1: Okay, I totally understand. Your health is important. You do know this was prescribed—

Speaker 2: By a doctor, though, correct? I do.

Speaker 1: Okay. They had to check out your medical history. I just wanted to make sure you did know that.

Speaker 2: So, because we do make sure this is safe before we send it out.

Speaker 2: Effects and I'm not comfortable with them. Okay.

Speaker 2: Just not bill or send it to you for, I mean, even up to like a half a year and give you—

Speaker 1: Some time to figure things out.

Speaker 2: No, no. No, I want to close it out.

Speaker 1: I want to close it out now.

Speaker 2: Okay. All right. We'll do that for you, sir.

Speaker 1: Anything else you need?

Speaker 2: No. Will I get a confirmation in my email?

Speaker 1: No email confirmation, no. Just a verbal one that everything is canceled here.

Speaker 1: You will never receive this again.

Speaker 2: Okay. All right. Thank you very much.

Speaker 1: You're welcome. Have a good day.
